    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-02T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-02T08:00:00-05:00" n="829"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d829">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11413: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-02T21:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 2, 1937—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 2—2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1070. Your number 599, December 1, 1 [<hi rend="italic">8</hi>] p.m. I have
                    repeatedly discussed the matter with my colleague who, however, can do nothing
                    in the face of the high military decision. The parade is scheduled to start at
                    11 o’clock tomorrow morning from Jessfield and to take 2 hours to pass down
                    Yuya-ching Road, Avenue Haig, Avenue Foch, Thibet Road, Nanking Road and the
                    Bund to Hongkew. About 3,000 men will be in line. Extraordinary police
                    precautions are being taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
